A '''Cache-cœur''' ([[French language|French]] for "hide the heart") is a [[top (clothing)|top]] for women, composed of two finished triangular parts, each having a strap.  It is closed by overlapping the two segments and tying the straps behind the back or along the side, depending on the length.  The triangular shape of the sides makes the garment a type of V-neck.

